      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>PART I, LINE 2:</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>RCS FOSTER PARENTS MUST COMPLETE A MINIMUM OF 33 HOURS OF TRAINING, DEPENDENT ON LEVEL OF CARE, AND UNDERGO A THOROUGH BACKGROUND AND PSYCHOLOGICAL ASSESSMENT BEFORE BEING APPROVED UNDER DEPARTMENT OF SOCIAL SERVICES, COMMUNITY CARE LICENSING BRANCH. THE YOUTH AUTHORIZED REPRESENTATIVE PROVIDES NECESSARY INFORMATION TO RCS TO ASSIST IN DETERMINING THE BEST MATCH. WHEN A YOUTH JOINS AN RCS RESOURCE FAMILY, PLACEMENT PAPERWORK IS SIGNED BY BOTH PARTIES. WHEN A YOUTH IS REUNIFYING WITH FAMILY, THE AUTHORIZED REPRESENTATIVE NOTIFIES RCS, AND A DISCHARGE DATE IS CONFIRMED. RCS RECEIVES DOCUMENTATION FROM COUNTY ELIGIBILITY CONFIRMING PLACEMENT DATES AND ENDING DATES. THE AMOUNT OF THE MONTHLY STIPEND PROVIDED TO THE RESOURCE PARENTS IS DEPENDENT ON THE LEVEL OF CARE AND DURATION OF PLACEMENT OF EACH YOUTH.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
    </IRS990ScheduleI>
